Problem:
--------
Implement pow(x, n), which calculates x raised to the power n (i.e., xn).

Example 1:
Input: x = 2.00000, n = 10
Output: 1024.00000

Example 2:
Input: x = 2.10000, n = 3
Output: 9.26100

Constraints:
-100.0 < x < 100.0
-231 <= n <= 231-1
n is an integer.
Either x is not zero or n > 0.
-10^4 <= xn <= 10^4

Solution:
--------
class Solution {
    public double pow(double x,long n){
        if(n==0){
            return 1.0;
        }
        if(n==1){
            return x;
        }
        if(n%2==0){
           return pow(x*x,n/2);
        }
        return x*pow(x*x,n/2);
    }
    public double myPow(double x, int n) {
        if(n<0){
            return 1.0/pow(x,-n);
        }
        return pow(x,n);
    }
}
Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(log n)
